5 Subject: Motor vehicles; secondary enforcement; searches
6 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to designate
7 certain motor vehicle violations as violations that may only be enforced if a
8 law enforcement officer has detained the operator of a vehicle for another
9 suspected violation. This bill also proposes to prohibit law enforcement
10 officers from requesting consent for a search of a vehicle or vehicle operator or
11 passenger following a stop for a moving violation.
12 An act relating to secondary enforcement of certain motor vehicle violations
13 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
14 Sec. 1. 23 V.S.A. § 9 is added to read:
15 § 9. SECONDARY ENFORCEMENT OF VIOLATIONS
16 (a) The following offenses may be enforced only if a law enforcement
17 officer has detained the operator of a motor vehicle for another suspected
18 violation:
19 (1) section 307 of this title (failure to carry a registration certificate);
